July 2023 evaluating of a baseline and two sensitivity scenarios 

WRFOUT_Default_LOCUSHDVMOD_Renewal_CTM.ipynb  visualizes the differences in meteorological vars
July2023_Renewal_NewBaseline-shareable.ipynb   visualizes the differences in pollutant species 
Emission_Validation.ipynb visualizes the emissions (emis_mole files + inln files converted to 2d) 

ModelingScenarios.png  Summarizes the three scenarios and emission modifications incorporated 
              Default dataset is the 2022v1 Emission Modeling Platform from the EPA
              LOCUS + HDV Mod uses (1) telemetry data to modify the magnitude and spatial footprint of MHDV idling within Illinois and
                                   (2) uses total combination truck AADT to spatially distribute combination truck on-road emissions
                                   Emission modifications for idling are within Illinois, on-road combination truck modifications are within the whole domain
              Renewal used MOVES to generate new emission factors within Cook and collar counties to represent an accelerated turn over of HDVs
                                    where all pre-2010 model year vehicles are replaced with model year 2022.
                                    Emission modifications are only within the Cook and collar counties.

ModelingScenarios_EmissionLevers.png Visualization of the emission modifications to provide a sense of where emissions are changing, 
              breaking down each step between modifying idling, combination truck on-road emissions, then both modifications together. 
              
